142581.s_name: European CDC  Situation Update Worldwide  Last updated 21 July, 09:38 (London time)

source.name: European CDC  Situation Update Worldwide  Last updated 21 July, 09:38 (London time)
source.dataPublishedBy: European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC)
source.additionalInfo: Raw data on confirmed cases and deaths for all countries is sourced from the European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC). Our complete COVID-19 dataset is a collection of the COVID-19 data maintained by Our World in Data. It is updated daily and includes data on confirmed cases, deaths, and testing. We have created a new description of all our data sources. You find it at our GitHub repository here. There you can download all of our data.

142927.name: Daily new estimated deaths due to COVID-19 (ICL)
142927.description: Values are for the mean estimate. For the US and LMICs, forecasts are for the policy scenario in which current mobility levels are maintained.

source.name: Imperial College London, COVID-19 Estimates (2020)
source.dataPublishedBy: MRC Centre for Global Infectious Disease Analysis, Imperial College London
source.additionalInfo:
Data from Imperial College London (ICL) estimating the number of COVID-19 infections and deaths for 122 countries.

For 11 European countries, estimates are as of 4 May 2020. More details can be found at https://mrc-ide.github.io/covid19estimates/#/ and in Flaxman, S., Mishra, S., Gandy, A. et al. (2020). Estimating the effects of non-pharmaceutical interventions on COVID-19 in Europe. Nature https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-020-2405-7.

For the United States, estimates are as of 29 May 2020 and were aggregated from individual US state estimates by Our World in Data. More details can be found at https://mrc-ide.github.io/covid19usa/#/.

For 110 low- and middle-income countries (LMICs), estimates are as of 21 Jun 2020. More details can be found at https://mrc-ide.github.io/global-lmic-reports/.
